      "explanation": "着(zhe) is placed after a verb to describe an ongoing state or the manner in which an action is performed. Structure: Verb + 着(zhe). It is different from 在(zài) + verb (which describes an action in progress). 着(zhe) often describes a continuous state: 门开着(the door is open), 他站着(he is standing).",
